&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;ROYAL BROMPTON HOSPITAL&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Occupational Therapist &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;BAND 7 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;£45,780 - £51,393 inc. HCAS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;JOB REF: 312-RB-0407&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full-time &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Permanent &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and talented Occupational Therapist who wishes to develop their knowledge in cardiorespiratory care and to work at this highly specialist hospital. The post covers a varied caseload within our respiratory medicine team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We need talent, dedication and an appetite to continually evaluate working practices to ensure a safe and quality service. You will be work amongst a highly experienced and vibrant MDT and be supported in your role by senior (B7) therapists, a therapy lead and a professional lead OT. You will be encouraged, as part of this clinical post to engage in audit, research and innovation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have the opportunity to develop your skills - supervising students, MDT working, audit/research and being involved in in-service training and MDT team teaching programs. Attendance at internal and external courses is encouraged.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is based at the Royal Brompton as part of the Rehab and Therapies Lung Team. This team works alongside our MDT in ILD, Sleep and Ventilation, Bronchiectasis, Asthma and COPD. This post holder would provide therapy leadership in our consultant led COVID-19 survivor clinic. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Core OT skills for assessment and treatment, rehabilitation and discharge planning are required utilising skills in both physical health and mental health assessment. In addition skills working in chronic conditions and vocational assessment would be desired. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;With a comprehensive induction and ongoing supervision and training to meet your learning needs, you will gain experience treating a variety of cardiorespiratory conditions. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date: 12th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We reserve the right to expire vacancies prior to the advertised closing date if a sufficient number of applications have been received. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Potential interview date week if the 20th November&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information or an informal chat please contact Bhavin Mehta (b.mehta@rbht.nhs.uk)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
